4279//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
4280// NVPTX DAG Combining
4281//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
4282
4283bool NVPTXTargetLowering::allowFMA(MachineFunction &MF,
4284 CodeGenOpt::Level OptLevel) const {
4285 // Always honor command-line argument
4286 if (FMAContractLevelOpt.getNumOccurrences() > 0)
4287 return FMAContractLevelOpt > 0;
4288
4289 // Do not contract if we're not optimizing the code.
4290 if (OptLevel == 0)
4291 return false;
4292
4293 // Honor TargetOptions flags that explicitly say fusion is okay.
4294 if (MF.getTarget().Options.AllowFPOpFusion == FPOpFusion::Fast)
4295 return true;
4296
4297 return allowUnsafeFPMath(MF);
4298}
4299
4300bool NVPTXTargetLowering::allowUnsafeFPMath(MachineFunction &MF) const {
4301 // Honor TargetOptions flags that explicitly say unsafe math is okay.
4302 if (MF.getTarget().Options.UnsafeFPMath)
4303 return true;
4304
4305 // Allow unsafe math if unsafe-fp-math attribute explicitly says so.
4306 const Function &F = MF.getFunction();
4307 if (F.hasFnAttribute("unsafe-fp-math")) {
4308 Attribute Attr = F.getFnAttribute("unsafe-fp-math");
4309 StringRef Val = Attr.getValueAsString();
4310 if (Val == "true")
4311 return true;
4312 }
4313
4314 return false;
4315}
4316
4317/// PerformADDCombineWithOperands - Try DAG combinations for an ADD with
4318/// operands N0 and N1. This is a helper for PerformADDCombine that is
4319/// called with the default operands, and if that fails, with commuted
4320/// operands.
4321static SDValue PerformADDCombineWithOperands(SDNode *N, SDValue N0, SDValue N1,
4322 TargetLowering::DAGCombinerInfo &DCI,
4323 const NVPTXSubtarget &Subtarget,
4324 CodeGenOpt::Level OptLevel) {
4325 SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
4326 // Skip non-integer, non-scalar case
4327 EVT VT=N0.getValueType();
4328 if (VT.isVector())
4329 return SDValue();
4330
4331 // fold (add (mul a, b), c) -> (mad a, b, c)
4332 //
4333 if (N0.getOpcode() == ISD::MUL) {
4334 assert (VT.isInteger());
4335 // For integer:
4336 // Since integer multiply-add costs the same as integer multiply
4337 // but is more costly than integer add, do the fusion only when
4338 // the mul is only used in the add.
4339 if (OptLevel==CodeGenOpt::None || VT != MVT::i32 ||
4340 !N0.getNode()->hasOneUse())
4341 return SDValue();
4342
4343 // Do the folding
4344 return DAG.getNode(NVPTXISD::IMAD, SDLoc(N), VT,
4345 N0.getOperand(0), N0.getOperand(1), N1);
4346 }
4347 else if (N0.getOpcode() == ISD::FMUL) {
4348 if (VT == MVT::f32 || VT == MVT::f64) {
4349 const auto *TLI = static_cast<const NVPTXTargetLowering *>(
4350 &DAG.getTargetLoweringInfo());
4351 if (!TLI->allowFMA(DAG.getMachineFunction(), OptLevel))
4352 return SDValue();
4353
4354 // For floating point:
4355 // Do the fusion only when the mul has less than 5 uses and all
4356 // are add.
4357 // The heuristic is that if a use is not an add, then that use
4358 // cannot be fused into fma, therefore mul is still needed anyway.
4359 // If there are more than 4 uses, even if they are all add, fusing
4360 // them will increase register pressue.
4361 //
4362 int numUses = 0;
4363 int nonAddCount = 0;
4364 for (SDNode::use_iterator UI = N0.getNode()->use_begin(),
4365 UE = N0.getNode()->use_end();
4366 UI != UE; ++UI) {
4367 numUses++;
4368 SDNode *User = *UI;
4369 if (User->getOpcode() != ISD::FADD)
4370 ++nonAddCount;
4371 }
4372 if (numUses >= 5)
4373 return SDValue();
4374 if (nonAddCount) {
4375 int orderNo = N->getIROrder();
4376 int orderNo2 = N0.getNode()->getIROrder();
4377 // simple heuristics here for considering potential register
4378 // pressure, the logics here is that the differnce are used
4379 // to measure the distance between def and use, the longer distance
4380 // more likely cause register pressure.
4381 if (orderNo - orderNo2 < 500)
4382 return SDValue();
4383
4384 // Now, check if at least one of the FMUL's operands is live beyond the node N,
4385 // which guarantees that the FMA will not increase register pressure at node N.
4386 bool opIsLive = false;
4387 const SDNode *left = N0.getOperand(0).getNode();
4388 const SDNode *right = N0.getOperand(1).getNode();
4389
4390 if (isa<ConstantSDNode>(left) || isa<ConstantSDNode>(right))
4391 opIsLive = true;
4392
4393 if (!opIsLive)
4394 for (SDNode::use_iterator UI = left->use_begin(), UE = left->use_end(); UI != UE; ++UI) {
4395 SDNode *User = *UI;
4396 int orderNo3 = User->getIROrder();
4397 if (orderNo3 > orderNo) {
4398 opIsLive = true;
4399 break;
4400 }
4401 }
4402
4403 if (!opIsLive)
4404 for (SDNode::use_iterator UI = right->use_begin(), UE = right->use_end(); UI != UE; ++UI) {
4405 SDNode *User = *UI;
4406 int orderNo3 = User->getIROrder();
4407 if (orderNo3 > orderNo) {
4408 opIsLive = true;
4409 break;
4410 }
4411 }
4412
4413 if (!opIsLive)
4414 return SDValue();
4415 }
4416
4417 return DAG.getNode(ISD::FMA, SDLoc(N), VT,
4418 N0.getOperand(0), N0.getOperand(1), N1);
4419 }
4420 }
4421
4422 return SDValue();
4423}
4424
4425/// PerformADDCombine - Target-specific dag combine xforms for ISD::ADD.
4426///
4427static SDValue PerformADDCombine(SDNode *N,
4428 TargetLowering::DAGCombinerInfo &DCI,
4429 const NVPTXSubtarget &Subtarget,
4430 CodeGenOpt::Level OptLevel) {
4431 SDValue N0 = N->getOperand(0);
4432 SDValue N1 = N->getOperand(1);
4433
4434 // First try with the default operand order.
4435 if (SDValue Result =
4436 PerformADDCombineWithOperands(N, N0, N1, DCI, Subtarget, OptLevel))
4437 return Result;
4438
4439 // If that didn't work, try again with the operands commuted.
4440 return PerformADDCombineWithOperands(N, N1, N0, DCI, Subtarget, OptLevel);
4441}
4442
4443static SDValue PerformANDCombine(SDNode *N,
4444 TargetLowering::DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) {
4445 // The type legalizer turns a vector load of i8 values into a zextload to i16
4446 // registers, optionally ANY_EXTENDs it (if target type is integer),
4447 // and ANDs off the high 8 bits. Since we turn this load into a
4448 // target-specific DAG node, the DAG combiner fails to eliminate these AND
4449 // nodes. Do that here.
4450 SDValue Val = N->getOperand(0);
4451 SDValue Mask = N->getOperand(1);
4452
4453 if (isa<ConstantSDNode>(Val)) {
4454 std::swap(Val, Mask);
4455 }
4456
4457 SDValue AExt;
4458 // Generally, we will see zextload -> IMOV16rr -> ANY_EXTEND -> and
4459 if (Val.getOpcode() == ISD::ANY_EXTEND) {
4460 AExt = Val;
4461 Val = Val->getOperand(0);
4462 }
4463
4464 if (Val->isMachineOpcode() && Val->getMachineOpcode() == NVPTX::IMOV16rr) {
4465 Val = Val->getOperand(0);
4466 }
4467
4468 if (Val->getOpcode() == NVPTXISD::LoadV2 ||
4469 Val->getOpcode() == NVPTXISD::LoadV4) {
4470 ConstantSDNode *MaskCnst = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Mask);
4471 if (!MaskCnst) {
4472 // Not an AND with a constant
4473 return SDValue();
4474 }
4475
4476 uint64_t MaskVal = MaskCnst->getZExtValue();
4477 if (MaskVal != 0xff) {
4478 // Not an AND that chops off top 8 bits
4479 return SDValue();
4480 }
4481
4482 MemSDNode *Mem = dyn_cast<MemSDNode>(Val);
4483 if (!Mem) {
4484 // Not a MemSDNode?!?
4485 return SDValue();
4486 }
4487
4488 EVT MemVT = Mem->getMemoryVT();
4489 if (MemVT != MVT::v2i8 && MemVT != MVT::v4i8) {
4490 // We only handle the i8 case
4491 return SDValue();
4492 }
4493
4494 unsigned ExtType =
4495 cast<ConstantSDNode>(Val->getOperand(Val->getNumOperands()-1))->
4496 getZExtValue();
4497 if (ExtType == ISD::SEXTLOAD) {
4498 // If for some reason the load is a sextload, the and is needed to zero
4499 // out the high 8 bits
4500 return SDValue();
4501 }
4502
4503 bool AddTo = false;
4504 if (AExt.getNode() != nullptr) {
4505 // Re-insert the ext as a zext.
4506 Val = DCI.DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, SDLoc(N),
4507 AExt.getValueType(), Val);
4508 AddTo = true;
4509 }
4510
4511 // If we get here, the AND is unnecessary. Just replace it with the load
4512 DCI.CombineTo(N, Val, AddTo);
4513 }
4514
4515 return SDValue();
4516}
4517
4518static SDValue PerformREMCombine(SDNode *N,
4519 TargetLowering::DAGCombinerInfo &DCI,
4520 CodeGenOpt::Level OptLevel) {
4521 assert(N->getOpcode() == ISD::SREM || N->getOpcode() == ISD::UREM);
4522
4523 // Don't do anything at less than -O2.
4524 if (OptLevel < CodeGenOpt::Default)
4525 return SDValue();
4526
4527 SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
4528 SDLoc DL(N);
4529 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
4530 bool IsSigned = N->getOpcode() == ISD::SREM;
4531 unsigned DivOpc = IsSigned ? ISD::SDIV : ISD::UDIV;
4532
4533 const SDValue &Num = N->getOperand(0);
4534 const SDValue &Den = N->getOperand(1);
4535
4536 for (const SDNode *U : Num->uses()) {
4537 if (U->getOpcode() == DivOpc && U->getOperand(0) == Num &&
4538 U->getOperand(1) == Den) {
4539 // Num % Den -> Num - (Num / Den) * Den
4540 return DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, DL, VT, Num,
4541 DAG.getNode(ISD::MUL, DL, VT,
4542 DAG.getNode(DivOpc, DL, VT, Num, Den),
4543 Den));
4544 }
4545 }
4546 return SDValue();
4547}
4548
4549enum OperandSignedness {
4550 Signed = 0,
4551 Unsigned,
4552 Unknown
4553};
4554
4555/// IsMulWideOperandDemotable - Checks if the provided DAG node is an operand
4556/// that can be demoted to \p OptSize bits without loss of information. The
4557/// signedness of the operand, if determinable, is placed in \p S.
4558static bool IsMulWideOperandDemotable(SDValue Op,
4559 unsigned OptSize,
4560 OperandSignedness &S) {
4561 S = Unknown;
4562
4563 if (Op.getOpcode() == ISD::SIGN_EXTEND ||
4564 Op.getOpcode() == ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG) {
4565 EVT OrigVT = Op.getOperand(0).getValueType();
4566 if (OrigVT.getFixedSizeInBits() <= OptSize) {
4567 S = Signed;
4568 return true;
4569 }
4570 } else if (Op.getOpcode() == ISD::ZERO_EXTEND) {
4571 EVT OrigVT = Op.getOperand(0).getValueType();
4572 if (OrigVT.getFixedSizeInBits() <= OptSize) {
4573 S = Unsigned;
4574 return true;
4575 }
4576 }
4577
4578 return false;
4579}
4580
4581/// AreMulWideOperandsDemotable - Checks if the given LHS and RHS operands can
4582/// be demoted to \p OptSize bits without loss of information. If the operands
4583/// contain a constant, it should appear as the RHS operand. The signedness of
4584/// the operands is placed in \p IsSigned.
4585static bool AreMulWideOperandsDemotable(SDValue LHS, SDValue RHS,
4586 unsigned OptSize,
4587 bool &IsSigned) {
4588 OperandSignedness LHSSign;
4589
4590 // The LHS operand must be a demotable op
4591 if (!IsMulWideOperandDemotable(LHS, OptSize, LHSSign))
4592 return false;
4593
4594 // We should have been able to determine the signedness from the LHS
4595 if (LHSSign == Unknown)
4596 return false;
4597
4598 IsSigned = (LHSSign == Signed);
4599
4600 // The RHS can be a demotable op or a constant
4601 if (ConstantSDNode *CI = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(RHS)) {
4602 const APInt &Val = CI->getAPIntValue();
4603 if (LHSSign == Unsigned) {
4604 return Val.isIntN(OptSize);
4605 } else {
4606 return Val.isSignedIntN(OptSize);
4607 }
4608 } else {
4609 OperandSignedness RHSSign;
4610 if (!IsMulWideOperandDemotable(RHS, OptSize, RHSSign))
4611 return false;
4612
4613 return LHSSign == RHSSign;
4614 }
4615}
4616
4617/// TryMULWIDECombine - Attempt to replace a multiply of M bits with a multiply
4618/// of M/2 bits that produces an M-bit result (i.e. mul.wide). This transform
4619/// works on both multiply DAG nodes and SHL DAG nodes with a constant shift
4620/// amount.
4621static SDValue TryMULWIDECombine(SDNode *N,
4622 TargetLowering::DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) {
4623 EVT MulType = N->getValueType(0);
4624 if (MulType != MVT::i32 && MulType != MVT::i64) {
4625 return SDValue();
4626 }
4627
4628 SDLoc DL(N);
4629 unsigned OptSize = MulType.getSizeInBits() >> 1;
4630 SDValue LHS = N->getOperand(0);
4631 SDValue RHS = N->getOperand(1);
4632
4633 // Canonicalize the multiply so the constant (if any) is on the right
4634 if (N->getOpcode() == ISD::MUL) {
4635 if (isa<ConstantSDNode>(LHS)) {
4636 std::swap(LHS, RHS);
4637 }
4638 }
4639
4640 // If we have a SHL, determine the actual multiply amount
4641 if (N->getOpcode() == ISD::SHL) {
4642 ConstantSDNode *ShlRHS = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(RHS);
4643 if (!ShlRHS) {
4644 return SDValue();
4645 }
4646
4647 APInt ShiftAmt = ShlRHS->getAPIntValue();
4648 unsigned BitWidth = MulType.getSizeInBits();
4649 if (ShiftAmt.sge(0) && ShiftAmt.slt(BitWidth)) {
4650 APInt MulVal = APInt(BitWidth, 1) << ShiftAmt;
4651 RHS = DCI.DAG.getConstant(MulVal, DL, MulType);
4652 } else {
4653 return SDValue();
4654 }
4655 }
4656
4657 bool Signed;
4658 // Verify that our operands are demotable
4659 if (!AreMulWideOperandsDemotable(LHS, RHS, OptSize, Signed)) {
4660 return SDValue();
4661 }
4662
4663 EVT DemotedVT;
4664 if (MulType == MVT::i32) {
4665 DemotedVT = MVT::i16;
4666 } else {
4667 DemotedVT = MVT::i32;
4668 }
4669
4670 // Truncate the operands to the correct size. Note that these are just for
4671 // type consistency and will (likely) be eliminated in later phases.
4672 SDValue TruncLHS =
4673 DCI.DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, DemotedVT, LHS);
4674 SDValue TruncRHS =
4675 DCI.DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, DemotedVT, RHS);
4676
4677 unsigned Opc;
4678 if (Signed) {
4679 Opc = NVPTXISD::MUL_WIDE_SIGNED;
4680 } else {
4681 Opc = NVPTXISD::MUL_WIDE_UNSIGNED;
4682 }
4683
4684 return DCI.DAG.getNode(Opc, DL, MulType, TruncLHS, TruncRHS);
4685}
4686
4687/// PerformMULCombine - Runs PTX-specific DAG combine patterns on MUL nodes.
4688static SDValue PerformMULCombine(SDNode *N,
4689 TargetLowering::DAGCombinerInfo &DCI,
4690 CodeGenOpt::Level OptLevel) {
4691 if (OptLevel > 0) {
4692 // Try mul.wide combining at OptLevel > 0
4693 if (SDValue Ret = TryMULWIDECombine(N, DCI))
4694 return Ret;
4695 }
4696
4697 return SDValue();
4698}
4699
4700/// PerformSHLCombine - Runs PTX-specific DAG combine patterns on SHL nodes.
4701static SDValue PerformSHLCombine(SDNode *N,
4702 TargetLowering::DAGCombinerInfo &DCI,
4703 CodeGenOpt::Level OptLevel) {
4704 if (OptLevel > 0) {
4705 // Try mul.wide combining at OptLevel > 0
4706 if (SDValue Ret = TryMULWIDECombine(N, DCI))
4707 return Ret;
4708 }
4709
4710 return SDValue();
4711}
4712
4713static SDValue PerformSETCCCombine(SDNode *N,
4714 TargetLowering::DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) {
4715 EVT CCType = N->getValueType(0);
4716 SDValue A = N->getOperand(0);
4717 SDValue B = N->getOperand(1);
4718
4719 if (CCType != MVT::v2i1 || A.getValueType() != MVT::v2f16)
4720 return SDValue();
4721
4722 SDLoc DL(N);
4723 // setp.f16x2 returns two scalar predicates, which we need to
4724 // convert back to v2i1. The returned result will be scalarized by
4725 // the legalizer, but the comparison will remain a single vector
4726 // instruction.
4727 SDValue CCNode = DCI.DAG.getNode(NVPTXISD::SETP_F16X2, DL,
4728 DCI.DAG.getVTList(MVT::i1, MVT::i1),
4729 {A, B, N->getOperand(2)});
4730 return DCI.DAG.getNode(ISD::BUILD_VECTOR, DL, CCType, CCNode.getValue(0),
4731 CCNode.getValue(1));
4732}
4733
4734SDValue NVPTXTargetLowering::PerformDAGCombine(SDNode *N,
4735 DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
4736 CodeGenOpt::Level OptLevel = getTargetMachine().getOptLevel();
4737 switch (N->getOpcode()) {
4738 default: break;
4739 case ISD::ADD:
4740 case ISD::FADD:
4741 return PerformADDCombine(N, DCI, STI, OptLevel);
4742 case ISD::MUL:
4743 return PerformMULCombine(N, DCI, OptLevel);
4744 case ISD::SHL:
4745 return PerformSHLCombine(N, DCI, OptLevel);
4746 case ISD::AND:
4747 return PerformANDCombine(N, DCI);
4748 case ISD::UREM:
4749 case ISD::SREM:
4750 return PerformREMCombine(N, DCI, OptLevel);
4751 case ISD::SETCC:
4752 return PerformSETCCCombine(N, DCI);
4753 }
4754 return SDValue();
4755}
4756
4757/// ReplaceVectorLoad - Convert vector loads into multi-output scalar loads.
4758static void ReplaceLoadVector(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG,
4759 SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &Results) {
4760 EVT ResVT = N->getValueType(0);
4761 SDLoc DL(N);
4762
4763 assert(ResVT.isVector() && "Vector load must have vector type");
4764
4765 // We only handle "native" vector sizes for now, e.g. <4 x double> is not
4766 // legal. We can (and should) split that into 2 loads of <2 x double> here
4767 // but I'm leaving that as a TODO for now.
4768 assert(ResVT.isSimple() && "Can only handle simple types");
4769 switch (ResVT.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy) {
4770 default:
4771 return;
4772 case MVT::v2i8:
4773 case MVT::v2i16:
4774 case MVT::v2i32:
4775 case MVT::v2i64:
4776 case MVT::v2f16:
4777 case MVT::v2f32:
4778 case MVT::v2f64:
4779 case MVT::v4i8:
4780 case MVT::v4i16:
4781 case MVT::v4i32:
4782 case MVT::v4f16:
4783 case MVT::v4f32:
4784 case MVT::v8f16: // <4 x f16x2>
4785 // This is a "native" vector type
4786 break;
4787 }
4788
4789 LoadSDNode *LD = cast<LoadSDNode>(N);
4790
4791 Align Alignment = LD->getAlign();
4792 auto &TD = DAG.getDataLayout();
4793 Align PrefAlign = TD.getPrefTypeAlign(ResVT.getTypeForEVT(*DAG.getContext()));
4794 if (Alignment < PrefAlign) {
4795 // This load is not sufficiently aligned, so bail out and let this vector
4796 // load be scalarized. Note that we may still be able to emit smaller
4797 // vector loads. For example, if we are loading a <4 x float> with an
4798 // alignment of 8, this check will fail but the legalizer will try again
4799 // with 2 x <2 x float>, which will succeed with an alignment of 8.
4800 return;
4801 }
4802
4803 EVT EltVT = ResVT.getVectorElementType();
4804 unsigned NumElts = ResVT.getVectorNumElements();
4805
4806 // Since LoadV2 is a target node, we cannot rely on DAG type legalization.
4807 // Therefore, we must ensure the type is legal. For i1 and i8, we set the
4808 // loaded type to i16 and propagate the "real" type as the memory type.
4809 bool NeedTrunc = false;
4810 if (EltVT.getSizeInBits() < 16) {
4811 EltVT = MVT::i16;
4812 NeedTrunc = true;
4813 }
4814
4815 unsigned Opcode = 0;
4816 SDVTList LdResVTs;
4817 bool LoadF16x2 = false;
4818
4819 switch (NumElts) {
4820 default:
4821 return;
4822 case 2:
4823 Opcode = NVPTXISD::LoadV2;
4824 LdResVTs = DAG.getVTList(EltVT, EltVT, MVT::Other);
4825 break;
4826 case 4: {
4827 Opcode = NVPTXISD::LoadV4;
4828 EVT ListVTs[] = { EltVT, EltVT, EltVT, EltVT, MVT::Other };
4829 LdResVTs = DAG.getVTList(ListVTs);
4830 break;
4831 }
4832 case 8: {
4833 // v8f16 is a special case. PTX doesn't have ld.v8.f16
4834 // instruction. Instead, we split the vector into v2f16 chunks and
4835 // load them with ld.v4.b32.
4836 assert(EltVT == MVT::f16 && "Unsupported v8 vector type.");
4837 LoadF16x2 = true;
4838 Opcode = NVPTXISD::LoadV4;
4839 EVT ListVTs[] = {MVT::v2f16, MVT::v2f16, MVT::v2f16, MVT::v2f16,
4840 MVT::Other};
4841 LdResVTs = DAG.getVTList(ListVTs);
4842 break;
4843 }
4844 }
4845
4846 // Copy regular operands
4847 SmallVector<SDValue, 8> OtherOps(N->op_begin(), N->op_end());
4848
4849 // The select routine does not have access to the LoadSDNode instance, so
4850 // pass along the extension information
4851 OtherOps.push_back(DAG.getIntPtrConstant(LD->getExtensionType(), DL));
4852
4853 SDValue NewLD = DAG.getMemIntrinsicNode(Opcode, DL, LdResVTs, OtherOps,
4854 LD->getMemoryVT(),
4855 LD->getMemOperand());
4856
4857 SmallVector<SDValue, 8> ScalarRes;
4858 if (LoadF16x2) {
4859 // Split v2f16 subvectors back into individual elements.
4860 NumElts /= 2;
4861 for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumElts; ++i) {
4862 SDValue SubVector = NewLD.getValue(i);
4863 SDValue E0 = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, DL, EltVT, SubVector,
4864 DAG.getIntPtrConstant(0, DL));
4865 SDValue E1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, DL, EltVT, SubVector,
4866 DAG.getIntPtrConstant(1, DL));
4867 ScalarRes.push_back(E0);
4868 ScalarRes.push_back(E1);
4869 }
4870 } else {
4871 for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumElts; ++i) {
4872 SDValue Res = NewLD.getValue(i);
4873 if (NeedTrunc)
4874 Res = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, ResVT.getVectorElementType(), Res);
4875 ScalarRes.push_back(Res);
4876 }
4877 }
4878
4879 SDValue LoadChain = NewLD.getValue(NumElts);
4880
4881 SDValue BuildVec = DAG.getBuildVector(ResVT, DL, ScalarRes);
4882
4883 Results.push_back(BuildVec);
4884 Results.push_back(LoadChain);
4885}
4886
4887static void ReplaceINTRINSIC_W_CHAIN(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG,
4888 SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &Results) {
4889 SDValue Chain = N->getOperand(0);
4890 SDValue Intrin = N->getOperand(1);
4891 SDLoc DL(N);
4892
4893 // Get the intrinsic ID
4894 unsigned IntrinNo = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Intrin.getNode())->getZExtValue();
4895 switch (IntrinNo) {
4896 default:
4897 return;
4898 case Intrinsic::nvvm_ldg_global_i:
4899 case Intrinsic::nvvm_ldg_global_f:
4900 case Intrinsic::nvvm_ldg_global_p:
4901 case Intrinsic::nvvm_ldu_global_i:
4902 case Intrinsic::nvvm_ldu_global_f:
4903 case Intrinsic::nvvm_ldu_global_p: {
4904 EVT ResVT = N->getValueType(0);
4905
4906 if (ResVT.isVector()) {
4907 // Vector LDG/LDU
4908
4909 unsigned NumElts = ResVT.getVectorNumElements();
4910 EVT EltVT = ResVT.getVectorElementType();
4911
4912 // Since LDU/LDG are target nodes, we cannot rely on DAG type
4913 // legalization.
4914 // Therefore, we must ensure the type is legal. For i1 and i8, we set the
4915 // loaded type to i16 and propagate the "real" type as the memory type.
4916 bool NeedTrunc = false;
4917 if (EltVT.getSizeInBits() < 16) {
4918 EltVT = MVT::i16;
4919 NeedTrunc = true;
4920 }
4921
4922 unsigned Opcode = 0;
4923 SDVTList LdResVTs;
4924
4925 switch (NumElts) {
4926 default:
4927 return;
4928 case 2:
4929 switch (IntrinNo) {
4930 default:
4931 return;
4932 case Intrinsic::nvvm_ldg_global_i:
4933 case Intrinsic::nvvm_ldg_global_f:
4934 case Intrinsic::nvvm_ldg_global_p:
4935 Opcode = NVPTXISD::LDGV2;
4936 break;
4937 case Intrinsic::nvvm_ldu_global_i:
4938 case Intrinsic::nvvm_ldu_global_f:
4939 case Intrinsic::nvvm_ldu_global_p:
4940 Opcode = NVPTXISD::LDUV2;
4941 break;
4942 }
4943 LdResVTs = DAG.getVTList(EltVT, EltVT, MVT::Other);
4944 break;
4945 case 4: {
4946 switch (IntrinNo) {
4947 default:
4948 return;
4949 case Intrinsic::nvvm_ldg_global_i:
4950 case Intrinsic::nvvm_ldg_global_f:
4951 case Intrinsic::nvvm_ldg_global_p:
4952 Opcode = NVPTXISD::LDGV4;
4953 break;
4954 case Intrinsic::nvvm_ldu_global_i:
4955 case Intrinsic::nvvm_ldu_global_f:
4956 case Intrinsic::nvvm_ldu_global_p:
4957 Opcode = NVPTXISD::LDUV4;
4958 break;
4959 }
4960 EVT ListVTs[] = { EltVT, EltVT, EltVT, EltVT, MVT::Other };
4961 LdResVTs = DAG.getVTList(ListVTs);
4962 break;
4963 }
4964 }
4965
4966 SmallVector<SDValue, 8> OtherOps;
4967
4968 // Copy regular operands
4969
4970 OtherOps.push_back(Chain); // Chain
4971 // Skip operand 1 (intrinsic ID)
4972 // Others
4973 OtherOps.append(N->op_begin() + 2, N->op_end());
4974
4975 MemIntrinsicSDNode *MemSD = cast<MemIntrinsicSDNode>(N);
4976
4977 SDValue NewLD = DAG.getMemIntrinsicNode(Opcode, DL, LdResVTs, OtherOps,
4978 MemSD->getMemoryVT(),
4979 MemSD->getMemOperand());
4980
4981 SmallVector<SDValue, 4> ScalarRes;
4982
4983 for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumElts; ++i) {
4984 SDValue Res = NewLD.getValue(i);
4985 if (NeedTrunc)
4986 Res =
4987 DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, ResVT.getVectorElementType(), Res);
4988 ScalarRes.push_back(Res);
4989 }
4990
4991 SDValue LoadChain = NewLD.getValue(NumElts);
4992
4993 SDValue BuildVec =
4994 DAG.getBuildVector(ResVT, DL, ScalarRes);
4995
4996 Results.push_back(BuildVec);
4997 Results.push_back(LoadChain);
4998 } else {
4999 // i8 LDG/LDU
5000 assert(ResVT.isSimple() && ResVT.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy == MVT::i8 &&
5001 "Custom handling of non-i8 ldu/ldg?");
5002
5003 // Just copy all operands as-is
5004 SmallVector<SDValue, 4> Ops(N->op_begin(), N->op_end());
5005
5006 // Force output to i16
5007 SDVTList LdResVTs = DAG.getVTList(MVT::i16, MVT::Other);
5008
5009 MemIntrinsicSDNode *MemSD = cast<MemIntrinsicSDNode>(N);
5010
5011 // We make sure the memory type is i8, which will be used during isel
5012 // to select the proper instruction.
5013 SDValue NewLD =
5014 DAG.getMemIntrinsicNode(ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN, DL, LdResVTs, Ops,
5015 MVT::i8, MemSD->getMemOperand());
5016
5017 Results.push_back(DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, MVT::i8,
5018 NewLD.getValue(0)));
5019 Results.push_back(NewLD.getValue(1));
5020 }
5021 }
5022 }
5023}
5024
5025void NVPTXTargetLowering::ReplaceNodeResults(
5026 SDNode *N, SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &Results, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
5027 switch (N->getOpcode()) {
5028 default:
5029 report_fatal_error("Unhandled custom legalization");
5030 case ISD::LOAD:
5031 ReplaceLoadVector(N, DAG, Results);
5032 return;
5033 case ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN:
5034 ReplaceINTRINSIC_W_CHAIN(N, DAG, Results);
5035 return;
5036 }
5037}
